<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,1028,526,812]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
A comparison with specimens from the Frey collection (NMB), and the recent contribution by 
<bibRefCitation author="Magnano, L." box="[325,515,601,625]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="305 - 315" refId="ref6445" refString="Magnano, L. (2005): Tre nuove specie di Otiorhynchus (Podenobistus Reitter, 1912) di Turchia (Coleoptera Curculionidae). - Atti Accademia Roveretana Agiati, Roma. Serie 8 (5), B: 305 - 315." type="journal article" year="2005">Magnano (2005)</bibRefCitation>
to the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[716,873,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Podenobistus</emphasis>
Reitter, 1912 revealed, that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="FAUST" authorityYear="1899" box="[318,438,638,662]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Otiorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bleusei">
<emphasis box="[318,438,638,662]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">O. bleusei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reported from Rhode Island (
<collectingCountry box="[794,882,638,662]" name="Greece" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Greece</collectingCountry>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[951,1027,638,662]" name="Turkey" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Turkey</collectingCountry>
around 
<collectingRegion box="[235,292,676,700]" country="Turkey" name="Izmir" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Izmir</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Keskin, B. &amp; Cevik, I. E." box="[308,576,676,700]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="225 - 239" refId="ref6177" refString="Keskin, B. &amp; Cevik, I. E. (2007 b): Izmir Ili Otiorhynchus (Germar, 1822) (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Entiminae) cinsi faunasi uzerinde arastirmalar. - Turkiye Entomoloji Dergisi 31 (3): 225 - 239." type="journal article" year="2007">Keskin &amp; Cevik 2007b</bibRefCitation>
), near 
<collectingRegion box="[660,739,676,700]" country="Turkey" name="Denizli" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Denizli</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[801,873,676,700]" country="Turkey" name="Mugla" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mugla</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lodos, N. &amp; Onder, F. &amp; Pehlivan, E. &amp; Atalay, R." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref6340" refString="Lodos, N., Onder, F., Pehlivan, E. &amp; Atalay, R. (1978): Ege ve Marmara BOlgesinin Zararli BOcek Faunasinin Tesbiti Uzerinde Calismalar. - Ankara Zirai Mucadele Merkez Atelye ve Ikmal Mudurlugu Ofset Baski Tesisleri 301 pp." type="book" year="1978">Lodos &amp; al. 1978</bibRefCitation>
) is closest to the specimens from Samos (
<figureCitation box="[691,778,713,737]" captionStart="Figs 4" captionStartId="8.[181,218,1549,1567]" captionTargetBox="[231,988,116,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-13@8.[181,1065,113,1512]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 4 A–D. A Hypoglyptus sp.; B Otiorhynchus cf. bleusei FAUST, 1899; C and D normal and big sized (= polyploid?) specimens of Otiorhynchus ovalipennis (BOHEMAN, 1843). Photos: C. Germann." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5851466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5851466/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). However, the extent of the species’ variability is difficult to estimate; therefore the present determination remains uncertain.
</paragraph>
